Thalli up to 150 µm long from foot to apex of furthest perithecia. Receptacle consisting of 4–8 superposed cells, dividing bilaterally into secondary appendages or perithecia. Perithecia stout, less than three times long than broad. [Detailed descriptions: 
Scheloske 1969
; Santamaria 1991, 2003; 
Majewski 1994b
]

